===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[Μακεδονία]]''' (''Makedonia'') "highland", from '''[[μακεδνός]]''' (''makednos''), "high, tall", from [[Doric Greek]] '''[[μάκος]]''' (''makos''), "height, length"; in [[Ionic Greek]]: '''[[μήκος]]''' (''mekos''). In Greek mythology, '''[[Μακεδονία]]''' (''Makedonia'') was named after '''[[Μακεδών]]''' (''Makedon''), the [[patriarch]] of the Macedonians.

